28:22.995 --> 28:24.161
My God.

28:29.655 --> 28:31.354
And this is the Brazilian-themed

28:31.356 --> 28:33.178
aquatic recreation center.

28:34.460 --> 28:36.661
Mr. Robertson almost
took a trip to Brazil,

28:36.686 --> 28:39.053
but he didn't, because
he's afraid to fly.

28:39.055 --> 28:41.422
But he looked up some images online,

28:41.424 --> 28:43.807
and he was inspired to create this.

28:44.373 --> 28:46.827
This pool, in particular,
is his passion project,

28:46.829 --> 28:49.158
and he's very upset about being sued.

28:49.533 --> 28:50.898
When he advertised

28:50.900 --> 28:52.666
mountain views from the swim-up bar,

28:52.668 --> 28:54.268
he didn't realize there weren't any,

28:54.270 --> 28:55.836
because he's also afraid to swim.

28:55.838 --> 28:58.606
Are you sure there are no
mountain views from the bar?

28:58.608 --> 29:01.108
You know what, it's
hard to tell from here.

29:01.110 --> 29:03.244
I think I see a peak
between those buildings.

29:03.246 --> 29:05.613
Yeah, I see that, too.
Although, the closer we get to the bar,

29:05.615 --> 29:07.314
the more obstructed the view is.

29:07.316 --> 29:10.206
I think we need to get a
photo from the swim-up bar.

29:10.486 --> 29:11.819
- Yes.
- You know what?

29:11.821 --> 29:13.287
I have a swimsuit in my car.

29:13.289 --> 29:14.885
I'll just hop in and do it.
You wait here.

29:14.910 --> 29:17.096
Sir, you shouldn't
have to get in the pool.

29:17.260 --> 29:19.326
I'll grab a suit from the
gift shop and take care of it.

29:19.328 --> 29:20.405
Please.

29:20.446 --> 29:22.513
Let's both grab a suit.

29:22.671 --> 29:24.604
Gift shop's this way.

29:25.218 --> 29:27.535
- This place is great.
- Yeah, good score, Mom.

29:28.504 --> 29:31.639
- Oh, I'm so glad we did this.
- Me, too.

29:31.641 --> 29:33.811
Hey, here. This is perfect.

29:34.043 --> 29:35.409
You know, I just...

29:35.411 --> 29:37.545
I needed to get away from work, and...

29:37.705 --> 29:39.713
I mean, I love those people, I do,

29:39.715 --> 29:41.515
but, dear God,

29:41.682 --> 29:44.552
what a bunch of needy misfits.

29:44.554 --> 29:45.768
Ooh.

29:49.296 --> 29:50.994
Ah...

29:58.689 --> 30:02.798
- Oh, God!
- Honey?

30:05.713 --> 30:07.975
Oh... that is my boss.

30:08.197 --> 30:10.044
I called in sick... I don't
want him to see me and...

30:10.046 --> 30:12.807
Wait, who is that woman?

30:13.182 --> 30:14.915
What is going on?

30:14.917 --> 30:17.088
Oh, I don't know.

30:17.486 --> 30:19.502
That woman walks very evenly.

30:20.322 --> 30:23.122
She must have a tendency to pronate.

30:26.283 --> 30:27.995
If you're standing here,

30:27.997 --> 30:30.297
there's technically a bit of a view.

30:30.299 --> 30:33.500
- Right here, if you lean over.
- Great.

30:34.829 --> 30:36.562
You are so professional.

30:36.759 --> 30:38.826
Even in a swim-up bar. It's amazing.

30:39.008 --> 30:40.074
I'm sorry?

30:40.076 --> 30:41.410
Well, it's just that...

30:42.111 --> 30:43.978
some people in your position

30:43.980 --> 30:45.519
would behave differently.

30:45.855 --> 30:48.248
Some people, who I
definitely don't think about

30:48.250 --> 30:50.421
or talk about at all anymore,

30:50.620 --> 30:52.486
they would not have
gone into that gift shop

30:52.488 --> 30:55.022
and selected a conservative
one-piece, like you did.

30:55.024 --> 30:57.524
They would have picked
out a ridiculous bikini,

30:57.526 --> 30:59.468
and they'd be slinging their
boobs all over the place.

30:59.493 --> 31:01.962
- I'm sorry, what?
- And they'd be provoking me

31:01.964 --> 31:04.929
and zinging me and
challenging my world view.

31:06.002 --> 31:07.733
And warming my heart...

31:10.039 --> 31:12.303
Thank God that's not happening.

31:12.575 --> 31:14.675
Thank God I don't have
that in my life anymore.

31:19.139 --> 31:20.481
I'm sorry.

31:20.483 --> 31:22.725
I'm not crying. I'm not crying.

31:23.285 --> 31:25.357
It's just the chlorine
in this water is...

31:26.435 --> 31:30.443
Oh, sir, you're okay.

31:30.723 --> 31:33.057
I mean, I think you're okay.

31:33.121 --> 31:34.954
I don't know what's going on.

31:35.006 --> 31:36.764
You're crying, and
I'm in a bathing suit.

31:36.766 --> 31:38.098
How did this happen?

31:40.202 --> 31:43.070
Becky? I was thinking we
could do each other's toes.

31:43.072 --> 31:44.238
You've been drugging me.

31:46.254 --> 31:48.842
Oh, this makes so much sense, of course.

31:49.410 --> 31:51.434
Of course you didn't change.

31:52.551 --> 31:54.782
The only reason I was feeling
better is 'cause you gave me

31:54.784 --> 31:59.348
these drugs... that blitzed me
out and made my ears buzz.

31:59.373 --> 32:02.254
I had no choice. I
saw all your websites.

32:02.511 --> 32:04.892
Your suicide websites.

32:04.894 --> 32:06.193
I had to do something.

32:06.195 --> 32:08.429
So you gave me medication
without my consent?

32:08.431 --> 32:11.910
Lest you forget, young lady, we
have been through this before.

32:11.944 --> 32:13.911
That suicide attempt in college,

32:13.936 --> 32:16.403
and then you tried to
burn down someone's house.

32:16.405 --> 32:17.838
And each time, you refused help,

32:17.840 --> 32:19.073
so, yes, yes,

32:19.075 --> 32:21.475
I decided to give you
some of the anxiety pills

32:21.477 --> 32:23.477
that the doctor gave me
for the High Holidays.

32:23.479 --> 32:26.180
I just wanted to calm
you down so we could talk

32:26.182 --> 32:28.975
and I could convince
you to go away somewhere.

32:29.326 --> 32:31.919
Commit me?

32:31.921 --> 32:34.021
I'm sorry, you wanted to commit me?

32:34.023 --> 32:35.689
That is such a dramatic word.

32:36.975 --> 32:39.359
You made me think that you loved me.

32:40.990 --> 32:43.257
You gave me hope when I had none.

32:46.458 --> 32:48.291
And now that hope is gone.

32:48.402 --> 32:49.935
I do love you.

32:50.039 --> 32:52.372
- I'm just trying to help you.
- Help?

32:52.374 --> 32:54.174
You were never any help.

32:54.880 --> 32:56.513
Rebecca...

32:56.877 --> 32:58.979
Rebecca, wait!

32:59.410 --> 33:01.582
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

33:01.584 --> 33:03.550
I shouldn't be talking about this.

33:03.552 --> 33:05.552
It's just that I've been going
through a lot lately because...

33:05.554 --> 33:06.587
You know what?

33:06.589 --> 33:07.888
Don't tell me, okay?

33:07.890 --> 33:10.190
I think it's best if
we just call it a day

33:10.192 --> 33:11.759
and go back to the office.

33:11.761 --> 33:12.826
Corns!

33:12.828 --> 33:13.927
Neels!

33:13.929 --> 33:15.162
Yaya!

33:15.164 --> 33:16.363
Oh, God,

33:16.365 --> 33:18.157
these jack-holes.

33:18.182 --> 33:19.710
So that's your boss, Mom?

33:19.735 --> 33:21.368
And all of your coworkers?

33:21.370 --> 33:23.836
- Ee-yep.
- Very cool.

33:25.165 --> 33:27.040
Why are you all here?

33:27.042 --> 33:28.642
Well, you know, we never circled back

33:28.644 --> 33:30.944
about that conversation we
had about my relationship.

33:30.946 --> 33:33.046
And I followed you and
then they followed me,

33:33.048 --> 33:35.713
like the psychopaths that
they are. And here we are.

33:35.738 --> 33:38.452
I called dibs on talking to
you first, because I'm a woman,

33:38.454 --> 33:40.287
but they don't respect women or dibs.

33:40.289 --> 33:41.722
Cornelia, let's blow this joint,

33:41.724 --> 33:44.892
go into town, try on some
vintage bowling shirts to music.

33:44.894 --> 33:47.594
Dude, stop. She has three
children and a husband.

33:47.596 --> 33:48.962
But does he make you laugh?

33:48.964 --> 33:51.331
Cornelia, ignore him,
ignore both of them.

33:51.333 --> 33:52.566
You like me the most, right?

33:52.568 --> 33:54.968
I mean,
you and I have a bond, right?

33:54.970 --> 33:57.326
- We have a sisterhood.
- We have a... oh, what is this?

33:57.351 --> 33:59.807
Pick me! Pick me, Cornelia, pick me!

33:59.809 --> 34:01.562
You like me best. You like
me best, I know you do!

34:01.587 --> 34:02.470
No, I nominate me.

34:02.495 --> 34:04.244
No, honestly, you have
a connection with me.

34:04.246 --> 34:05.349
Like a therapy session
that I've never...

34:05.374 --> 34:06.346
I told you all
not to follow me.

34:07.416 --> 34:08.815
There's a very good chance...

34:08.818 --> 34:09.882
- Listen to me!
- Come on!

34:11.887 --> 34:13.085
Please!

34:13.088 --> 34:15.722
♪ I feel like this isn't about me ♪

34:15.724 --> 34:19.393
♪ I feel like this isn't about me ♪

34:19.395 --> 34:22.896
♪ Clearly they're projecting
all of their feelings ♪

34:22.898 --> 34:24.498
♪ About a person I've never met ♪

34:24.500 --> 34:27.367
♪ And making it about me ♪

34:27.369 --> 34:30.070
I'm telling you guys, from the
moment she walked in the room,

34:30.072 --> 34:32.472
there was just such chemistry.
It was love at first sight!

34:32.474 --> 34:35.475
♪ Bah, bah, bah,
bah, bah, bah, bah ♪

34:35.476 --> 34:39.012
♪ I'm not the best
with social cues ♪

34:39.014 --> 34:41.547
♪ But this one's pretty clear ♪

34:41.550 --> 34:43.550
♪ This isn't about her ♪

34:43.552 --> 34:44.851
♪ About her ♪

34:44.853 --> 34:48.422
♪ This reminds me to
try the Brazilian place ♪

34:48.424 --> 34:51.792
♪ With the live band and
the meat on the stick ♪

34:51.793 --> 34:54.127
♪ That they carve ♪

34:54.129 --> 34:57.731
♪ Right at the table ♪

34:57.733 --> 35:00.968
♪ Right at the table ♪

35:00.970 --> 35:04.037
♪ Right at the table ♪

35:04.039 --> 35:08.075
