35:11.881 --> 35:13.513
Hey!

35:13.515 --> 35:15.249
I'm going back to L.A.

35:15.251 --> 35:17.851
to file several HR complaints.

35:17.982 --> 35:20.487
I look forward to
collecting a settlement

35:20.489 --> 35:23.790
and finally opening up
my custom yo-yo business.

35:23.792 --> 35:26.526
You guys... are a mess.

35:26.621 --> 35:28.310
Bye!

35:29.677 --> 35:31.444
Have you been crying?

35:32.424 --> 35:33.834
Your eyes are all red.

35:33.836 --> 35:34.935
Oh, yeah.

35:34.937 --> 35:38.038
What the hell... is going on?

35:38.770 --> 35:40.536
I take one vacation!

35:41.510 --> 35:45.112
And, Jim, you... are ripped.

35:45.114 --> 35:48.181
- It's just protein shakes.
- Nice. They're working.

35:48.916 --> 35:50.248
Becky?

35:50.352 --> 35:51.783
Where are you?

35:53.088 --> 35:54.388
Rebecca Nora Bunch!

35:54.413 --> 35:56.613
Did you crawl out of
a window or something?

35:58.331 --> 36:00.397
Where did she go?

36:06.846 --> 36:10.470
- _
- What?

36:20.647 --> 36:23.504
Excuse me, miss? Are you okay?

36:26.889 --> 36:28.466
I don't know.

36:33.719 --> 36:37.771
Man, I take one fake
vacation for a few days

36:37.796 --> 36:40.663
and you guys lose your minds.

36:41.875 --> 36:44.210
- That poor woman.
- Yeah, I know.

36:44.235 --> 36:47.845
The thing is, Cornelia
reminded me of Rebecca.

36:47.847 --> 36:49.514
Reminded all of us of Rebecca.

36:49.516 --> 36:51.916
Not me. To me, she was 
the opposite of Rebecca,

36:51.918 --> 36:54.031
which only made me miss her even more.

36:54.056 --> 36:57.635
Look, we love her. We always will.

36:57.660 --> 37:01.429
But we have got to move on.

37:02.155 --> 37:04.762
She's got her life, we have ours.

37:04.764 --> 37:08.132
And maybe that has
just got to be enough.

37:08.134 --> 37:09.634
You're right.

37:10.077 --> 37:12.203
White Josh and I have got to
deal with our relationship.

37:12.205 --> 37:14.640
I'm gonna call him, I'm
gonna take him to a yurt,

37:14.757 --> 37:16.941
we're gonna take some
ayahuasca and figure it out,

37:16.943 --> 37:19.177
no matter how long it takes.

37:19.179 --> 37:20.511
Thank you, Paula.

37:27.691 --> 37:30.982
- It's not gonna be easy without her.
- Yeah.

37:32.701 --> 37:34.034
You okay?

37:36.362 --> 37:38.168
No, but I will be.

37:39.299 --> 37:43.980
I just hope, wherever
she is, she's happy.

37:46.621 --> 37:48.535
Actually, yeah, you can help me.

37:49.433 --> 37:51.409
This is gonna sound a
little crazy, but, um,

37:51.411 --> 37:52.777
I-I need to get off the plane.

37:52.779 --> 37:55.413
I bought a ticket to go to
L.A. when I was in New York.

37:55.415 --> 37:57.014
But I'm just remembering now,

37:57.016 --> 37:59.717
that everyone in L.A. either hates me

37:59.719 --> 38:01.808
and/or thinks I'm crazy, so,

38:01.833 --> 38:04.222
New York isn't my home,
but L.A. isn't either.

38:04.224 --> 38:06.224
So, all I need you to do,

38:06.226 --> 38:10.128
is just drop me off
in, like, Ohio or Idaho?

38:10.130 --> 38:11.229
In a cornfield somewhere.

38:11.231 --> 38:12.363
Sorry, hon.

38:12.365 --> 38:13.831
We really can't just drop people off.

38:13.833 --> 38:16.711
But you can get off the plane
in L.A. and buy a new ticket.

38:17.132 --> 38:18.836
True, true.

38:18.838 --> 38:19.992
Yeah.

38:20.306 --> 38:21.906
The thing is, I'm just too tired

38:21.908 --> 38:25.076
to... buy things or do
things or get things

38:25.078 --> 38:26.811
or say things or face things.

38:27.039 --> 38:31.616
Tell you what, we have
a Merlot that is...

38:31.618 --> 38:33.384
the only one we have.

38:34.110 --> 38:35.143
Do you want a glass of that?

38:35.168 --> 38:38.192
- Sure, that sounds great.
- I got you, girl.

38:51.057 --> 38:53.108
♪ ♪

39:13.420 --> 39:15.412
♪ ♪

39:37.126 --> 39:39.944
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

39:40.454 --> 39:42.020
Do you need anything else?

39:42.701 --> 39:43.867
No.

39:47.922 --> 39:50.055
